  "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
  "body": "I created a pod manifest with two containers, one that terminates quickly and another that continues running. I set the restartPolicy to \"onFailure.\" However, the pod status shows 'Waiting', even after waiting for the images to be pulled. According to [this](https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes/blob/master/pkg/api/v1beta3/types.go#L359), if at least one container is running in the pod, the pod state should be 'Running'.\n\n``` json\n{\n  \"id\": \"test-pod-status\",\n  \"kind\": \"Pod\",\n  \"apiVersion\": \"v1beta2\",\n  \"desiredState\": {\n    \"manifest\": {\n      \"version\": \"v1beta2\",\n      \"containers\": [{\n        \"name\": \"terminates\",\n        \"image\": \"busybox\"\n      },\n      {\n        \"name\": \"runs-forever\",\n        \"image\": \"kubernetes/pause\",\n      }],\n      \"restartPolicy\": {\n        \"onFailure\": {}\n      }\n    }\n  }\n}\n```\n\n**Steps to reproduce:**\n1. `$ cluster/kubcfg.sh -c test-pod-status.json create pods`\n2. `$ cluster/kubecfg list pods` will show\n\n```\nID                  Image(s)                          Host                                                                 Labels              Status\n----------          ----------                        ----------                                                           ----------          ----------\ntest-pod-status-1   busybox,kubernetes/pause          kubernetes-minion-1.c.read-eval-print-loop.internal/146.148.63.97                        Waiting\n```\n\n**Expected result:**\nStatus should show 'Running'.\n\n**Actual Result:**\nStatus shows 'Waiting'.\n",
